        "title": "fix(telegram): keep partial streams live when block defaults are on",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Telegram users who configured partial streaming could still see blocked delivery when a legacy global block-streaming default was enabled.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nTelegram now resolves block streaming through a Telegram-owned helper that lets explicit Telegram block-streaming config win, lets `streaming.mode: \"partial\"` or `\"progress\"` disable legacy block delivery, and keeps doctor warnings aligned with runtime behavior.\n\n## User Impact\n\nTelegram partial streaming now behaves as one live updating preview unless block streaming is explicitly enabled for Telegram. Existing explicit block-streaming setups continue to work.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot.helpers.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/doctor.test.ts` passed: 168 tests.\n- `git diff HEAD --check` passed.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode uncommitted --engine copilot` passed with no accepted/actionable findings.",
